{%- comment -%}
  snippets/cart-recommendations.liquid

  Renders the product recommendations shell inside the cart drawer.
  JS reads data-* attributes from the drawer root (#ecombio-cart-drawer)
  and from this container, then fetches and injects recommendation cards
  after the drawer opens — initial render is never blocked.

  Usage (inside cart-drawer.liquid, after the items list):
    {%- render 'cart-recommendations',
          show_related: show_related,
          show_complementary: show_complementary,
          related_label: related_label,
          complementary_label: complementary_label
    -%}

  Parameters:
    show_related        {Boolean} Render the "You may also like" rail
    show_complementary  {Boolean} Render the "Frequently bought together" rail
    related_label       {String}  Heading text for the related rail
    complementary_label {String}  Heading text for the complementary rail

  Notes:
    "related" intent        → Shopify ML, works out of the box.
    "complementary" intent  → Requires Shopify Search & Discovery app +
                              complementary products configured per product
                              in Admin → Products → [product] → Complementary
                              products. Returns 0 products silently when no
                              associations exist; the rail is hidden by JS.

    The source product ID is read from sessionStorage key
    'ecombio_last_added_product_id' (written by your ATC flow). Falls back
    to the first cart item's [data-cart-product-id] attribute.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- if show_related or show_complementary -%}
  <div
    class="ecombio-cart-recs"
    data-ecombio-recs
    data-related-label="{{ related_label | escape }}"
    data-complementary-label="{{ complementary_label | escape }}"
    aria-live="polite"
    aria-label="Product recommendations"
  >
    {%- comment -%}
      Skeleton renders immediately to prevent layout shift.
      JS replaces this entire block once recommendations load.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="ecombio-cart-recs__skeleton" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="ecombio-cart-recs__skeleton-bar"></div>
      <div class="ecombio-cart-recs__skeleton-cards">
        {%- for i in (1..4) -%}
          <div class="ecombio-cart-recs__skeleton-card"></div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}